<div class="la-wrapper la-wrapper--privacy">
  <div class="app-shell">
    <main class="la-main" role="main">

      <section class="la-section la-privacy-section">
        <div class="la-about-glass-card la-privacy-content-card">
          <div class="la-privacy-content">
            <div class="la-privacy-content-header">
              <span class="la-section-eyebrow-badge">
                {{t "Legal" key="legal"}} <span style="color: #2a5aa8;">Lingo</span><span style="color: #3a6bc7; font-style: italic;">Linq</span>
              </span>
              <h1 class="la-privacy-title">{{t "Privacy Policy" key="privacy_policy"}}</h1>
              <hr class="la-about-hero-separator" aria-hidden="true">
              <p class="la-privacy-updated">{{t "Last Updated: March 3, 2026" key="privacy_updated"}}</p>
            </div>
            <p>{{t "LingoLinq LLC (\"LingoLinq,\" \"we,\" \"us,\" or \"our\") is deeply committed to your privacy. This Privacy Policy applies to our website (www.lingolinq.com) and LingoLinq's products, software, and applications (collectively, the \"Product\")." key="privacy_intro"}}</p>

            <p>{{t "Because LingoLinq is utilized globally in educational and medical settings, we employ stringent data protection practices designed to comply with local, federal, and international regulations, including COPPA, FERPA, HIPAA, GDPR (Europe), and CCPA (California)." key="privacy_compliance"}}</p>

            <p>{{t "Our core privacy philosophy is simple: we never log your private conversations, and any usage data we collect to improve our Product is strictly anonymized and requires your explicit opt-in." key="privacy_philosophy"}}</p>

            <p>{{t "By using the Product, you agree to the collection and use of your information as described in this policy." key="privacy_agreement"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "1. The LingoLinq Privacy Guarantee" key="privacy_guarantee_heading"}}</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "The \"Private Thoughts\" Guarantee:" key="privacy_guarantee_thoughts_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq never logs, collects, or analyzes verbatim transcripts of a communicator's conversations or specific sentences generated. Your thoughts and words are yours alone." key="privacy_guarantee_thoughts"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Strict Separation of Users:" key="privacy_guarantee_separation_heading"}}</strong> {{t "We legally and technically separate the data of the \"Account Administrator\" (e.g., the parent, therapist, or school district) from the \"Communicator\" (the AAC user). Marketing, billing data, and website cookies apply only to the Account Administrator. The Communicator's interface is free of tracking pixels, advertising, and marketing." key="privacy_guarantee_separation"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "2. Information We Collect" key="privacy_collect_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "We collect the minimum personal information needed to operate LingoLinq securely:" key="privacy_collect_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Account Information:" key="privacy_collect_account_heading"}}</strong> {{t "To establish a secure login, we collect the username, email address, and password from the Account Administrator. (We encourage organizations to use anonymized usernames for Communicators)." key="privacy_collect_account"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "User-Generated Content:" key="privacy_collect_ugc_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Vocabulary boards, custom buttons, profile summaries, and uploaded media are stored securely for access across various devices." key="privacy_collect_ugc"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Biometric & Sensor Data (Local Processing Only):" key="privacy_collect_biometric_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If enabled for accessibility, LingoLinq uses device sensors for head position, eye gaze, and facial expression tracking. We do not collect, store, or share Biometric Identifiers or Biometric Information. This data is processed dynamically on your local device to facilitate screen selection and is immediately discarded." key="privacy_collect_biometric"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Anonymized App Analytics:" key="privacy_collect_analytics_heading"}}</strong> {{t "If you explicitly opt-in, we collect automated, generalized telemetry data (e.g., how often certain app features are used). This data is stripped of personal identifiers and pooled into an aggregate format to help us improve the Product." key="privacy_collect_analytics"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "3. How We Use Your Information" key="privacy_use_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "We use the information we collect to:" key="privacy_use_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li>{{t "Provide, troubleshoot, and support your specific LingoLinq account;" key="privacy_use_provide"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "Sync and back up your User-Generated Content securely across your devices;" key="privacy_use_sync"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "Facilitate secure sharing only between a communicator and their authorized support team (e.g., designated therapists or parents);" key="privacy_use_share"}}</li>
              <li>{{t "Comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Use." key="privacy_use_legal"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "4. Sharing & Third-Party Processors" key="privacy_sharing_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "We only share information with authorized users (like assigned supervisors) and vetted third-party service providers who help us operate LingoLinq. These providers are bound by strict Data Processing Agreements (DPAs). No Personally Identifiable Information (PII) or Protected Health Information (PHI) is ever sent to our analytics providers." key="privacy_sharing_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Cloud Hosting & Storage:" key="privacy_sharing_cloud_heading"}}</strong> {{t "for core app hosting, secure database management, and encrypted file storage;" key="privacy_sharing_cloud"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Data Processing:" key="privacy_sharing_data_heading"}}</strong> {{t "for translating boards, and transcoding media;" key="privacy_sharing_data"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Analytics & Logging:" key="privacy_sharing_analytics_heading"}}</strong> {{t "for tracking app errors and system health (strictly anonymized data only);" key="privacy_sharing_analytics"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Support & Communications:" key="privacy_sharing_support_heading"}}</strong> {{t "for customer service and account-related email/SMS notifications (Admin only)." key="privacy_sharing_support"}}</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>{{t "Business Transfers:" key="privacy_sharing_transfers_heading"}}</strong> {{t "In the event that LingoLinq is involved in a merger, acquisition, sale of assets, or bankruptcy, your information may be transferred to the acquiring entity. We will notify you via email and/or a prominent notice on our Product of any change in ownership or uses of your personal information, as well as any choices you may have regarding your personal information." key="privacy_sharing_transfers"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "5. Special Privacy Protections (HIPAA, FERPA, COPPA)" key="privacy_special_heading"}}</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Health Information (HIPAA):" key="privacy_special_hipaa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "For covered medical professionals, LingoLinq operates as a Business Associate. User-generated content is encrypted in transit (SSL) and at rest. We will execute Business Associate Agreements (BAAs) with eligible healthcare organizations upon request." key="privacy_special_hipaa"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Educational Records (FERPA):" key="privacy_special_ferpa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "When LingoLinq is used by schools, we act as a \"School Official\" with a legitimate educational interest. We maintain the confidentiality of student records and use data strictly to provide the contracted educational services." key="privacy_special_ferpa"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Children's Privacy (COPPA):" key="privacy_special_coppa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "Children under 13 may only use LingoLinq with verifiable consent from a parent, guardian, or authorized school official. If we learn we have collected personal information from a child under 13 without proper consent, we will delete it promptly." key="privacy_special_coppa"}}</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>{{t "Disclaimer of Absolute Security:" key="privacy_special_disclaimer_heading"}}</strong> {{t "While LingoLinq utilizes commercially acceptable, industry-standard means to protect your personal information, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute security against sophisticated, unforeseen cyberattacks or zero-day vulnerabilities." key="privacy_special_disclaimer"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "6. International and State Privacy Rights (GDPR, CCPA)" key="privacy_rights_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "Depending on your location, you have specific rights regarding your personal data. Where LingoLinq acts as a Data Controller (for direct, individual subscribers) or a Data Processor (for schools and clinics), we guarantee the following rights:" key="privacy_rights_intro"}}</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Right to Know and Access:" key="privacy_rights_access_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You can request a copy of the personal data we hold about you." key="privacy_rights_access"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Right to Deletion (\"Right to be Forgotten\"):" key="privacy_rights_deletion_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You can request the permanent deletion of your account and personal data at any time." key="privacy_rights_deletion"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Right to Correction:" key="privacy_rights_correction_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You may update or correct inaccurate data within your profile settings." key="privacy_rights_correction"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Right to Data Portability:" key="privacy_rights_portability_heading"}}</strong> {{t "You may request a secure export of your data in a structured, commonly used format." key="privacy_rights_portability"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "\"Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information\" (CCPA):" key="privacy_rights_ccpa_heading"}}</strong> {{t "LingoLinq does not sell your personal information, nor do we share it for cross-context behavioral advertising." key="privacy_rights_ccpa"}}</li>
            </ul>
            <p>{{t "To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at support@lingolinq.com. We will respond within the timeframes required by applicable law." key="privacy_rights_contact"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "7. Data Security, Retention, and Breach Notification" key="privacy_security_heading"}}</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>{{t "Security:" key="privacy_security_security_heading"}}</strong> {{t "We utilize industry-standard encryption, secure cloud infrastructure, and strict internal access controls to protect your account." key="privacy_security_security"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Retention:" key="privacy_security_retention_heading"}}</strong> {{t "We retain active accounts indefinitely. Accounts inactive for 12 months are flagged for automatic deletion. Upon deletion, your personal data is purged (subject to a 10-day grace period for accidental deletions)." key="privacy_security_retention"}}</li>
              <li><strong>{{t "Incident Response:" key="privacy_security_incident_heading"}}</strong> {{t "In the unlikely event of a security breach that exposes personal information or results in data loss, LingoLinq will notify affected users and organization administrators via email within 72 hours of confirming the incident, providing details and a remediation plan." key="privacy_security_incident"}}</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>{{t "8. Third-Party Links and Integrations" key="privacy_thirdparty_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "The Product may contain links to or allow you to launch third-party websites, applications, or services (such as YouTube or external web pages) that are not operated by LingoLinq. If you click a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit." key="privacy_thirdparty"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "9. Changes to This Privacy Policy" key="privacy_changes_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. If we make a material change, we will provide you with prominent notice (email or an in-app notification) prior to the change becoming effective and update the \"Last Updated\" date at the top of this page." key="privacy_changes"}}</p>

            <h3>{{t "10. Contact Us" key="privacy_contact_heading"}}</h3>
            <p>{{t "If you have questions, data deletion requests, or compliance inquiries, please contact our Data Privacy Team:" key="privacy_contact_intro"}}</p>
            <p class="la-privacy-address">
              {{t "Email:" key="privacy_contact_email_label"}} <a href="mailto:support@lingolinq.com">support@lingolinq.com</a><br>
              {{t "Phone:" key="privacy_contact_phone_label"}} (801) 739-5307<br>
              {{t "Mail:" key="privacy_contact_mail_label"}} LingoLinq LLC, 5041 Taylor Ave, Ogden, UT 84403
            </p>

            <p>{{t "© 2026 LingoLinq LLC. All rights reserved." key="privacy_copyright"}}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</div>
